OAmetrics 0.4.4

    • JIF
    • Computing the similarity of papers to an author's core set
  • Changelog

    JIF

    Source: vignettes/JIF.Rmd
    JIF.Rmd
    knitr::opts_chunk$set(cache = TRUE)
    library(OAmetrics)
    ## Loading required package: data.table
    ## This is OAmetrics 0.4.4
    ## OAmetrics is BETA software! Please report any bugs.
    # Scientific Reports. According to website the JIF is 3.8 in 2023
res <- data.frame()
for (l in c(100, 500, 1000, 5000, 10000)) {
  for (r in 1:20) {
    start <- Sys.time()
    res0 <- get_JIF(issn="2045-2322", year=2023, limit=l, seed=r)
    end <- Sys.time()
    res0$dur <- end-start
    res0$limit <- l
    res <- rbind(res, res0)
    print(res)
    flush.console()
  }
}
